  "body": "\r\nSolidity\r\n\r\n```\r\n//SPDX-License-Identifier: Unlicense\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.7;\r\ncontract Greeter {\r\n    string private greeting;\r\n    constructor(string memory _greeting) {\r\n        greeting = _greeting;\r\n    }\r\n    error GreetError(string msg);\r\n    function greet() public view returns (string memory) {\r\n      revert GreetError(greeting);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nTest\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst { ethers } = require(\"hardhat\");\r\n\r\ndescribe(\"Greeter\", function () {\r\n  it(\"Should return the new greeting once it's changed\", async function () {\r\n    const Greeter = await ethers.getContractFactory(\"Greeter\");\r\n    const greeter = await Greeter.deploy(\"Hello, world!\");\r\n    await greeter.deployed();    \r\n    try{\r\n      await greeter.greet();\r\n    }catch(e){\r\n      console.log(e.message)\r\n      console.log(Object.keys(e));\r\n    }\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe test result\r\n\r\n```\r\n$npx hardhat test\r\n\r\n\r\n  Greeter\r\nVM Exception while processing transaction: reverted with custom error 'GreetError(\"Hello, world!\")'\r\n[ 'stackTrace' ]\r\n    âœ“ Should return the new greeting once it's changed (1922ms)\r\n\r\n\r\n  1 passing (2s)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAccording to https://blog.ricmoo.com/highlights-ethers-js-may-2021-2826e858277d, ethers.js should decode the custom error and should add attributes like `errorName`, `code`, `errorArgs` but the error in the est only has `stackTrace`.\r\n\r\n",
