    "body": "With this issue unresolved, it's effectively impossible to automatically handle custom errors in code that relies on Hardhat. If Hardhat knows the ABI of the `Error` object it will print out a handy message, but either way there's no way for a program to catch the revert and read the arguments to the custom error type.\r\n\r\nIn order to be [compatible with ethers](https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/master/packages/contracts/src.ts/index.ts#L388) and in line with other implementations, it should [return the error data from eth_call as the result](https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/master/packages/abi/src.ts/interface.ts#L403). Alternately it could return the error data as a property on the exception that is thrown, which would be incompatible with the RPC interface of other nodes, but at least make catching and interpreting revert reasons *possible*.\r\n\r\nWhat can we do to get this fixed/implemented? Would posting a bounty be useful?",
