    "body": "In the meantime, anyone looking for a workaround can try this:\r\n```\r\n//SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\n\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\n\r\ncontract RevertProxy {\r\n    function call(address payable target, bytes calldata data) external payable returns(bytes memory) {\r\n        (, bytes memory response) = target.call{value:msg.value}(data);\r\n        return response;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nDeploy that to your hardhat node and make calls via it, and any reverts will be turned into returns, and handled by Ethers etc as expected.",
