    "body": "> You can enable this behavior by setting networks.hardhat.throwOnCallFailures to false in your config. There's also networks.hardhat.throwOnTransactionFailures. When building Hardhat Network we decided to copy Ganache's non-standard behavior for compatibility reasons but added these options to let users opt-in into a more standard behavior.\r\n\r\nThis is true - but it means that you can't recover error data at all if these options are on. What you suggest later would make the most sense. If you include the raw revert data, Ethers can add support for decoding it easily.",
